<div class="about">
<p class="about__text">We Americans can't agree which way is up anymore. Here's why:</p>
<div class="about__image-container">
	<img class="about__image" src="/assets/permanent/left1-151d14412c.jpg" width="750" height="332" alt="Hillary Clinton saying 'We need more clean energy jobs'."/>
	<img class="about__image" src="/assets/permanent/left2-1def3ac295.jpg" width="750" height="332" alt="Sean Hannity saying 'Hillary Clinton wants to kill coal jobs'."/>
</div>
<p class="about__text">Our politicians say one thing, the media twists it around, and our fellow citizens believe the lies. The trouble is, politicians and advertisers are selling us each our own set of lies, tailored to divide us further.</p>
<p class="about__text">Take the cartoon above. We showed it to you because, based on where you live, you probably voted for Clinton.  Here's what we show your fellow citizens in conservative Texas:</p>
<div class="about__image-container">
	<img class="about__image" src="/assets/permanent/right1-958db900d8.jpg" width="750" height="332" alt="Donald Trump saying 'We need to protect our borders'."/>
	<img class="about__image" src="/assets/permanent/right2-437e5d030e.jpg" width="750" height="332" alt="Rachel Maddow saying 'Donald Trump says all Mexicans are rapists.'"/>
</div>
<p class="about__text">MyTake.org is a radically transparent platform for citizens to speak their mind without political parties getting in the way. Here's how it works:<p>
<div class="about__image-container">
	<img class="about__image" src="/assets/permanent/bias_overlap-547e900409.png" width="323" height="219"/>
</div>
<ul class="about__list">
	<li class="about__list-item">We start with a <span class="about__text about__text--special">Foundation</span> of unbiased <span class="about__text about__text--special">Facts</span> everyone can agree on. Only the following make the cut:
		<ul class="about__sub-list">
		<li class="about__sub-list-item">The United States Constitution.</li>
		<li class="about__sub-list-item">Every televised presidential debate.  Always the full original source.  No spin, no analysis, no cherrypicking.</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li class="about__list-item">Give your <span class="about__text about__text--special">Take</span>, and make it more convincing by adding snippets from this unbiased <span class="about__text about__text--special">Foundation</span>.  You can't link to anything besides this <span class="about__text about__text--special">Foundation</span>.</li>
	<li class="about__list-item">Share your <span class="about__text about__text--special">Take</span> with friends, get their <span class="about__text about__text--special">Take</span> back.</li>
</ul>
<p class="about__text">Our only goal is to build a place where we can have civil disagreements based in reality.  How can you trust us?  You don't, just see for yourself.<p>
<ul class="about__list">
	<li class="about__list-item">You can see the full source code for this site, and all the discussions which created it <a class="about__link" href="https://github.com/mytakedotorg/mytakedotorg">right here</a>.</li>
	<li class="about__list-item">We publish every financial transaction we've ever made <a class="about__link" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1l1IErsVZNlaVKsZQSubGEaidIp_5z3hQGInchDWn39A/edit?usp=sharing">right here</a>.</li>
	<li class="about__list-item">Want to help us make the site better? Talk about how MyTake should work over at <a class="about__linl" href="https://meta.mytake.org/">meta.mytake.org</a>.</li>
</ul>
</div>


